        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare multi-system disorder characterized by oculocutaneous albinism bleeding diathesis and in some cases neutropenia pulmonary fibrosis or granulomatous colitis. The clinical subtypes of Hermansky-Pudlak syndrome (HPS) often present the same clinical phenotype but have different associated complications with varying degrees of severity."
        },
